36 /* Peripheral: AAR */
37 /* Description: Accelerated Address Resolver */
38 
39 /* Register: AAR_INTENSET */
40 /* Description: Enable interrupt */
41 
42 /* Bit 2 : Write '1' to Enable interrupt for NOTRESOLVED event */
43 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Pos (2UL)
44 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Pos)
45 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Disabled (0UL)
46 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Enabled (1UL)
47 #define AAR_INTENSET_NOTRESOLVED_Set (1UL)
49 /* Bit 1 : Write '1' to Enable interrupt for RESOLVED event */
50 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Pos (1UL)
51 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Pos)
52 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Disabled (0UL)
53 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Enabled (1UL)
54 #define AAR_INTENSET_RESOLVED_Set (1UL)
56 /* Bit 0 : Write '1' to Enable interrupt for END event */
57 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Pos (0UL)
58 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENSET_END_Pos)
59 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Disabled (0UL)
60 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Enabled (1UL)
61 #define AAR_INTENSET_END_Set (1UL)
63 /* Register: AAR_INTENCLR */
64 /* Description: Disable interrupt */
65 
66 /* Bit 2 : Write '1' to Disable interrupt for NOTRESOLVED event */
67 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Pos (2UL)
68 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Pos)
69 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Disabled (0UL)
70 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Enabled (1UL)
71 #define AAR_INTENCLR_NOTRESOLVED_Clear (1UL)
73 /* Bit 1 : Write '1' to Disable interrupt for RESOLVED event */
74 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Pos (1UL)
75 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Pos)
76 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Disabled (0UL)
77 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Enabled (1UL)
78 #define AAR_INTENCLR_RESOLVED_Clear (1UL)
80 /* Bit 0 : Write '1' to Disable interrupt for END event */
81 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Pos (0UL)
82 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Msk (0x1UL << AAR_INTENCLR_END_Pos)
83 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Disabled (0UL)
84 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Enabled (1UL)
85 #define AAR_INTENCLR_END_Clear (1UL)
87 /* Register: AAR_STATUS */
88 /* Description: Resolution status */
89 
90 /* Bits 3..0 : The IRK that was used last time an address was resolved */
91 #define AAR_STATUS_STATUS_Pos (0UL)
92 #define AAR_STATUS_STATUS_Msk (0xFUL << AAR_STATUS_STATUS_Pos)
94 /* Register: AAR_ENABLE */
95 /* Description: Enable AAR */
96 
97 /* Bits 1..0 : Enable or disable AAR */
98 #define AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Pos (0UL)
99 #define AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Msk (0x3UL << AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Pos)
100 #define AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Disabled (0UL)
101 #define AAR_ENABLE_ENABLE_Enabled (3UL)
103 /* Register: AAR_NIRK */
104 /* Description: Number of IRKs */
105 
106 /* Bits 4..0 : Number of Identity root keys available in the IRK data structure */
107 #define AAR_NIRK_NIRK_Pos (0UL)
108 #define AAR_NIRK_NIRK_Msk (0x1FUL << AAR_NIRK_NIRK_Pos)
110 /* Register: AAR_IRKPTR */
111 /* Description: Pointer to IRK data structure */
112 
113 /* Bits 31..0 : Pointer to the IRK data structure */
114 #define AAR_IRKPTR_IRKPTR_Pos (0UL)
115 #define AAR_IRKPTR_IRKPTR_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << AAR_IRKPTR_IRKPTR_Pos)
117 /* Register: AAR_ADDRPTR */
118 /* Description: Pointer to the resolvable address */
119 
120 /* Bits 31..0 : Pointer to the resolvable address (6-bytes) */
121 #define AAR_ADDRPTR_ADDRPTR_Pos (0UL)
122 #define AAR_ADDRPTR_ADDRPTR_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << AAR_ADDRPTR_ADDRPTR_Pos)
124 /* Register: AAR_SCRATCHPTR */
125 /* Description: Pointer to data area used for temporary storage */
126 
127 /* Bits 31..0 : Pointer to a scratch data area used for temporary storage during resolution.A space of minimum 3 bytes must be reserved. */
128 #define AAR_SCRATCHPTR_SCRATCHPTR_Pos (0UL)
129 #define AAR_SCRATCHPTR_SCRATCHPTR_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << AAR_SCRATCHPTR_SCRATCHPTR_Pos)
132 /* Peripheral: ACL */
133 /* Description: Access control lists */
134 
135 /* Register: ACL_DISABLEINDEBUG */
136 /* Description: Disable all ACL protection mechanisms for regions while in debug mode */
137 
138 /* Bit 0 : Disable the protection mechanism for regions while in debug mode. */
139 #define ACL_DISABLEINDEBUG_DISABLEINDEBUG_Pos (0UL)
140 #define ACL_DISABLEINDEBUG_DISABLEINDEBUG_Msk (0x1UL << ACL_DISABLEINDEBUG_DISABLEINDEBUG_Pos)
141 #define ACL_DISABLEINDEBUG_DISABLEINDEBUG_Enabled (0UL)
142 #define ACL_DISABLEINDEBUG_DISABLEINDEBUG_Disabled (1UL)
144 /* Register: ACL_ACL_ADDR */
145 /* Description: Description cluster[0]: Configure the word-aligned start address of region 0 to protect */
146 
147 /* Bits 31..0 : Valid word-aligned start address of region 0 to protect. Address must point to a flash page boundary. */
148 #define ACL_ACL_ADDR_ADDR_Pos (0UL)
149 #define ACL_ACL_ADDR_ADDR_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << ACL_ACL_ADDR_ADDR_Pos)
151 /* Register: ACL_ACL_SIZE */
152 /* Description: Description cluster[0]: Size of region to protect counting from address ACL[0].ADDR. Write '0' as no effect. */
153 
154 /* Bits 31..0 : Size of flash region 0 in bytes. Must be a multiple of the flash page size. */
155 #define ACL_ACL_SIZE_SIZE_Pos (0UL)
156 #define ACL_ACL_SIZE_SIZE_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << ACL_ACL_SIZE_SIZE_Pos)
158 /* Register: ACL_ACL_PERM */
159 /* Description: Description cluster[0]: Access permissions for region 0 as defined by start address ACL[0].ADDR and size ACL[0].SIZE */
160 
161 /* Bit 2 : Configure read permissions for region 0. Write '0' has no effect. */
162 #define ACL_ACL_PERM_READ_Pos (2UL)
163 #define ACL_ACL_PERM_READ_Msk (0x1UL << ACL_ACL_PERM_READ_Pos)
164 #define ACL_ACL_PERM_READ_Enable (0UL)
165 #define ACL_ACL_PERM_READ_Disable (1UL)
167 /* Bit 1 : Configure write and erase permissions for region 0. Write '0' has no effect. */
168 #define ACL_ACL_PERM_WRITE_Pos (1UL)
169 #define ACL_ACL_PERM_WRITE_Msk (0x1UL << ACL_ACL_PERM_WRITE_Pos)
170 #define ACL_ACL_PERM_WRITE_Enable (0UL)
171 #define ACL_ACL_PERM_WRITE_Disable (1UL)
174 /* Peripheral: CCM */
175 /* Description: AES CCM Mode Encryption */
176 
177 /* Register: CCM_SHORTS */
178 /* Description: Shortcut register */
179 
180 /* Bit 0 : Shortcut between ENDKSGEN event and CRYPT task */
181 #define CCM_SHORTS_ENDKSGEN_CRYPT_Pos (0UL)
182 #define CCM_SHORTS_ENDKSGEN_CRYPT_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_SHORTS_ENDKSGEN_CRYPT_Pos)
183 #define CCM_SHORTS_ENDKSGEN_CRYPT_Disabled (0UL)
184 #define CCM_SHORTS_ENDKSGEN_CRYPT_Enabled (1UL)
186 /* Register: CCM_INTENSET */
187 /* Description: Enable interrupt */
188 
189 /* Bit 2 : Write '1' to Enable interrupt for ERROR event */
190 #define CCM_INTENSET_ERROR_Pos (2UL)
191 #define CCM_INTENSET_ERROR_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_INTENSET_ERROR_Pos)
192 #define CCM_INTENSET_ERROR_Disabled (0UL)
193 #define CCM_INTENSET_ERROR_Enabled (1UL)
194 #define CCM_INTENSET_ERROR_Set (1UL)
196 /* Bit 1 : Write '1' to Enable interrupt for ENDCRYPT event */
197 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDCRYPT_Pos (1UL)
198 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDCRYPT_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_INTENSET_ENDCRYPT_Pos)
199 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDCRYPT_Disabled (0UL)
200 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDCRYPT_Enabled (1UL)
201 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDCRYPT_Set (1UL)
203 /* Bit 0 : Write '1' to Enable interrupt for ENDKSGEN event */
204 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDKSGEN_Pos (0UL)
205 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDKSGEN_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_INTENSET_ENDKSGEN_Pos)
206 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDKSGEN_Disabled (0UL)
207 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDKSGEN_Enabled (1UL)
208 #define CCM_INTENSET_ENDKSGEN_Set (1UL)
210 /* Register: CCM_INTENCLR */
211 /* Description: Disable interrupt */
212 
213 /* Bit 2 : Write '1' to Disable interrupt for ERROR event */
214 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ERROR_Pos (2UL)
215 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ERROR_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_INTENCLR_ERROR_Pos)
216 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ERROR_Disabled (0UL)
217 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ERROR_Enabled (1UL)
218 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ERROR_Clear (1UL)
220 /* Bit 1 : Write '1' to Disable interrupt for ENDCRYPT event */
221 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDCRYPT_Pos (1UL)
222 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDCRYPT_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_INTENCLR_ENDCRYPT_Pos)
223 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDCRYPT_Disabled (0UL)
224 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDCRYPT_Enabled (1UL)
225 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDCRYPT_Clear (1UL)
227 /* Bit 0 : Write '1' to Disable interrupt for ENDKSGEN event */
228 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDKSGEN_Pos (0UL)
229 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDKSGEN_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_INTENCLR_ENDKSGEN_Pos)
230 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDKSGEN_Disabled (0UL)
231 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDKSGEN_Enabled (1UL)
232 #define CCM_INTENCLR_ENDKSGEN_Clear (1UL)
234 /* Register: CCM_MICSTATUS */
235 /* Description: MIC check result */
236 
237 /* Bit 0 : The result of the MIC check performed during the previous decryption operation */
238 #define CCM_MICSTATUS_MICSTATUS_Pos (0UL)
239 #define CCM_MICSTATUS_MICSTATUS_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_MICSTATUS_MICSTATUS_Pos)
240 #define CCM_MICSTATUS_MICSTATUS_CheckFailed (0UL)
241 #define CCM_MICSTATUS_MICSTATUS_CheckPassed (1UL)
243 /* Register: CCM_ENABLE */
244 /* Description: Enable */
245 
246 /* Bits 1..0 : Enable or disable CCM */
247 #define CCM_ENABLE_ENABLE_Pos (0UL)
248 #define CCM_ENABLE_ENABLE_Msk (0x3UL << CCM_ENABLE_ENABLE_Pos)
249 #define CCM_ENABLE_ENABLE_Disabled (0UL)
250 #define CCM_ENABLE_ENABLE_Enabled (2UL)
252 /* Register: CCM_MODE */
253 /* Description: Operation mode */
254 
255 /* Bit 24 : Packet length configuration */
256 #define CCM_MODE_LENGTH_Pos (24UL)
257 #define CCM_MODE_LENGTH_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_MODE_LENGTH_Pos)
258 #define CCM_MODE_LENGTH_Default (0UL)
259 #define CCM_MODE_LENGTH_Extended (1UL)
261 /* Bits 17..16 : Radio data rate that the CCM shall run synchronous with */
262 #define CCM_MODE_DATARATE_Pos (16UL)
263 #define CCM_MODE_DATARATE_Msk (0x3UL << CCM_MODE_DATARATE_Pos)
264 #define CCM_MODE_DATARATE_1Mbit (0UL)
265 #define CCM_MODE_DATARATE_2Mbit (1UL)
266 #define CCM_MODE_DATARATE_125Kbps (2UL)
267 #define CCM_MODE_DATARATE_500Kbps (3UL)
269 /* Bit 0 : The mode of operation to be used. The settings in this register apply whenever either the KSGEN or CRYPT tasks are triggered. */
270 #define CCM_MODE_MODE_Pos (0UL)
271 #define CCM_MODE_MODE_Msk (0x1UL << CCM_MODE_MODE_Pos)
272 #define CCM_MODE_MODE_Encryption (0UL)
273 #define CCM_MODE_MODE_Decryption (1UL)
275 /* Register: CCM_CNFPTR */
276 /* Description: Pointer to data structure holding AES key and NONCE vector */
277 
278 /* Bits 31..0 : Pointer to the data structure holding the AES key and the CCM NONCE vector (see Table 1 CCM data structure overview) */
279 #define CCM_CNFPTR_CNFPTR_Pos (0UL)
280 #define CCM_CNFPTR_CNFPTR_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << CCM_CNFPTR_CNFPTR_Pos)
282 /* Register: CCM_INPTR */
283 /* Description: Input pointer */
284 
285 /* Bits 31..0 : Input pointer */
286 #define CCM_INPTR_INPTR_Pos (0UL)
287 #define CCM_INPTR_INPTR_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << CCM_INPTR_INPTR_Pos)
289 /* Register: CCM_OUTPTR */
290 /* Description: Output pointer */
291 
292 /* Bits 31..0 : Output pointer */
293 #define CCM_OUTPTR_OUTPTR_Pos (0UL)
294 #define CCM_OUTPTR_OUTPTR_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << CCM_OUTPTR_OUTPTR_Pos)
296 /* Register: CCM_SCRATCHPTR */
297 /* Description: Pointer to data area used for temporary storage */
298 
299 /* Bits 31..0 : Pointer to a scratch data area used for temporary storage during key-stream generation, MIC generation and encryption/decryption. */
300 #define CCM_SCRATCHPTR_SCRATCHPTR_Pos (0UL)
301 #define CCM_SCRATCHPTR_SCRATCHPTR_Msk (0xFFFFFFFFUL << CCM_SCRATCHPTR_SCRATCHPTR_Pos)
303 /* Register: CCM_MAXPACKETSIZE */
304 /* Description: Length of key-stream generated when MODE.LENGTH = Extended. */
305 
306 /* Bits 7..0 : Length of key-stream generated when MODE.LENGTH = Extended. This value must be greater or equal to the subsequent packet to be encrypted/decrypted. */
307 #define CCM_MAXPACKETSIZE_MAXPACKETSIZE_Pos (0UL)
308 #define CCM_MAXPACKETSIZE_MAXPACKETSIZE_Msk (0xFFUL << CCM_MAXPACKETSIZE_MAXPACKETSIZE_Pos)
310 /* Register: CCM_RATEOVERRIDE */
311 /* Description: Data rate override setting. */
312 
313 /* Bits 1..0 : Data rate override setting. */
314 #define CCM_RATEOVERRIDE_RATEOVERRIDE_Pos (0UL)
315 #define CCM_RATEOVERRIDE_RATEOVERRIDE_Msk (0x3UL << CCM_RATEOVERRIDE_RATEOVERRIDE_Pos)
316 #define CCM_RATEOVERRIDE_RATEOVERRIDE_1Mbit (0UL)
317 #define CCM_RATEOVERRIDE_RATEOVERRIDE_2Mbit (1UL)
318 #define CCM_RATEOVERRIDE_RATEOVERRIDE_125Kbps (2UL)
319 #define CCM_RATEOVERRIDE_RATEOVERRIDE_500Kbps (3UL)

437 /* Register: CLOCK_LFCLKSRCCOPY */

440 /* Bits 1..0 : Clock source */

442 #define CLOCK_LFCLKSRCCOPY_SRC_Msk (0x3UL << CLOCK_LFCLKSRCCOPY_SRC_Pos)

448 /* Register: CLOCK_LFCLKSRC */
449 /* Description: Clock source for the LFCLK */
450 
451 /* Bit 17 : Enable or disable external source for LFCLK */
452 #define CLOCK_LFCLKSRC_EXTERNAL_Pos (17UL)
453 #define CLOCK_LFCLKSRC_EXTERNAL_Msk (0x1UL << CLOCK_LFCLKSRC_EXTERNAL_Pos)
454 #define CLOCK_LFCLKSRC_EXTERNAL_Disabled (0UL)
455 #define CLOCK_LFCLKSRC_EXTERNAL_Enabled (1UL)
457 /* Bit 16 : Enable or disable bypass of LFCLK crystal oscillator with external clock source */
458 #define CLOCK_LFCLKSRC_BYPASS_Pos (16UL)
